<HEADLINE> Rapids 2, Fire 1  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHICAGO (AP) -- Former Chicago forward Junior Agogo had a goal
and an assist as the Colorado Rapids beat the Chicago Fire 2-1 on
Wednesday night in Major League Soccer.
</P>
<P>
   Agogo, traded to Colorado on April 10 for a draft choice, opened
the scoring in the 18th minute and set up Jorge Dely Valdez's goal
in the 71st minute. Lubos Kubik scored for Chicago in the 78th
minute.
</P>
<P>
   Colorado improved to 4-4-0 and Chicago dropped to 3-4-1.
</P>
<P>
   A crowd of 5,144 attended the game at Soldier Field.
</P>
</TEXT>
