<HEADLINE> Stocks Open Narrowly Mixed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened narrowly mixed with the
Dow Jones industrial average up 10 points in today's early going.
Advancing issues on the New York Stock Exchange hold a 4-3 lead
over decliners.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off 4 points.
</P>
<P>
   Stocks appear to have enough upside momentum from late yesterday
to offset some fairly uninspiring numbers on the economy.
</P>
<P>
   The government reported that worker productivity rose in the
first quarter, but by a smaller measure than had been expected.
</P>
<P>
   So, even with the higher interest rate implications of that
report, Wall Street is edging higher.
</P>
<P>
   It may be that the selling seen earlier this week has left the
market with little downside risk for the immediate future.
</P>
<P>
   Also, there are some favorable earnings to study. Disney
reported better-than-expected profits for the first quarter.
</P>
