<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Music festival promoters' pitch hits sour note with localofficials  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   AUBURN, N.Y. (AP) -- The promoters of a benefit music festival
have failed to apply for the proper permits and cannot put on the
three-day concert, say local officials.
</P>
<P>
   An attorney for one of the promoters said Cayuga County and Town
of Brutus officials may have to go to court to block the show.
</P>
<P>
   ''They may have to sue us to stop,'' attorney Andrew Fusco said
Wednesday following a 90-minute meeting with local officials.
</P>
<P>
   As many as 65 local and regional bands were expected to play at
the event July 3-5 during the county fair. The bands agreed to play
for free and proceeds would have benefited local food pantries.
About 1,000 to 3,000 people were expected.
</P>
<P>
   Local officials, however, became alarmed when they found the
show was being advertised on the World Wide Web as ''the biggest
indie (independent) music festival ever.'' Officials said they
feared the event could turn into another Woodstock '99, which drew
nearly 250,000 people to Rome last summer and ended in a fiery
riot. Officials also said they have had past problems with rock
concerts at the county fairgrounds.
</P>
<P>
   At Wednesday's meeting, officials said promoters did not apply
for two state permits regulating mass gatherings and overnight
camping. They also said promoters needed a mass-gathering permit
and a zoning variance from the town.
</P>
<P>
   ''We feel holding the concert is illegal,'' said County Attorney
Thomas P. Stopyra. ''You know we have to try to protect the
public.''
</P>
<P>
   Glenn Donnelly, one of the promoters, said the turn of events
was shocking.
</P>
<P>
   ''I can't believe it. This is unbelievable it's even
happening,'' Donnelly said.
</P>
<P>
   Donnelly runs The Agricultural Society of the County of Cayuga,
which is in charge of the county fairgrounds and adjoining
speedway. He said he has been putting on concerts and other events
at the fairgrounds for over 20 years without a problem.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-05-04-00 1047 </TRAILER>
