<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-04 12:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> N.J. man gets prison for crash that killed son  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   WILLIAMSPORT, Pa. (AP) -- A Jersey Shore area man who wrecked his
car while drunk, killing his 1-year-old son, was sentenced to serve
three to seven years in state prison.
</P>
<P>
   David E. Butler, 35, pleaded guilty to homicide by motor vehicle
while driving under the influence, aggravated assault by motor
vehicle while driving under the influence, homicide by vehicle and
other charges.
</P>
<P>
   Butler's attorney told him he could have had some of the lesser
charges dismissed, but Butler disagreed, telling Lycoming County
Judge Kenneth D. Brown that he wanted to ''face up to'' the
charges. He was also ordered to attend alcohol and grief counseling
in prison, and to pay more than $1,200 in fines.
</P>
<P>
   Police said Butler's blood-alcohol content was 0.09 percent --
just under the legal limit -- when he fell asleep and lost control
of his car Nov. 20. The vehicle went off a bridge and rolled over
an embankment.
</P>
<P>
   Butler admitted to drinking three quarts of beer earlier before
taking his son and stepson out for a ride to look for deer. His
son, Dakota, died of massive injuries suffered in the accident.
James E. Craver, 9, Butler's stepson, suffered serious injuries in
the accident as well.
</P>
<P>
   Butler said both children were wearing seat belts, but police
said Dakota was not properly placed in his child safety seat.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-05-04-00 1251 </TRAILER>
