<HEADLINE> James Postl Named CEO Of Pennzoil  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON (AP) -- James J. Postl, a former Nabisco and PepsiCo
executive, has been promoted to chief executive officer of
Pennzoil-Quaker State Co.
</P>
<P>
   Postl has been president and chief operating officer of
Houston-based Pennzoil since 1998. He takes over June 1 as CEO to
succeed James L. Pate, who will remain chairman, the company said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   After coming to Pennzoil, Postl took over a major restructuring
effort that included the merger of Quaker State with Pennzoil's
motor oil, refined products and franchise operations.
</P>
<P>
   The marriage, completed in January 1999, created a company with
annual sales of $3.2 billion and brought together the No. 1 and No.
2-selling brands of motor oil.
</P>
<P>
   Prior to joining Pennzoil, Postl was president of Nabisco
Biscuit Co. and earlier, president and CEO of Nabisco
International. For 19 years, he held numerous management positions
with PepsiCo.
</P>
<P>
   He began his career as a brand manager with Procter &AMP; Gamble Co.
</P>
</TEXT>
