<BODY>
<HEADLINE> One Killed in La. Tour Bus Crash  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SLIDELL, La. (AP) -- A bus taking 48 elderly tourists to New
Orleans collided with a car Thursday, killing the car's driver and
injuring 13 bus passengers.
</P>
<P>
   The bus crushed the rear half of the car on Interstate 10 near
Slidell, about 20 miles north of New Orleans. State police said the
car had been moving erratically for some distance and stopped
abruptly in front of the bus, leaving no room for the bus to avoid
it.
</P>
<P>
   The car was fully ablaze when firefighters arrived 10 minutes
later, and the driver's body was burnt beyond recognition, said
Neil Ricca of the St. Tammany Parish fire department.
</P>
<P>
   The injured bus passengers were taken to hospitals. The most
serious injury was a broken shoulder, said Ann Barks, spokeswoman
for Slidell Memorial Hospital.
</P>
<P>
   The bus passengers were from the New York-New Jersey area and
were mostly in their 70s. They had gambled at area casinos and were
traveling to New Orleans for sightseeing.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
