<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Orioles' Erickson Activated From DL  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BALTIMORE (AP) -- The Baltimore Orioles activated Scott Erickson
off the 15-day disabled list Thursday and handed him an imposing
opening assignment: The right-hander will make his season debut
Friday night at Yankee Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   Erickson, the No. 2 starter in the rotation, had bone chips
removed from his right elbow on March 3. His only action this year
came in two rehabilitation assignments in the minor leagues.
</P>
<P>
   ''I don't see taking him much over 120, 125 pitches,'' Orioles
manager Mike Hargrove said. ''He's pitched well against New York in
New York before and he's a very intense competitor, so we'll find
out real quick.''
</P>
<P>
   To make room for Erickson on the roster, the Orioles optioned
right-handed reliever Gabe Molina to Triple-A Rochester.
</P>
<P>
   Molina has lived the life of a yo-yo this season. He was sent to
Rochester on March 28 and recalled April 7. Molina was again
optioned to Rochester on April 17, but recalled on the 28th.
</P>
<P>
   Now he's headed back to the minors.
</P>
<P>
   ''Here or Rochester, I just want a chance to compete,'' Molina
said. ''I like to be out there pitching.''
</P>
</TEXT>
