<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Miramax Extends Disney Agreement  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The brothers behind such big screen hits as
''Shakespeare in Love'' and ''Scream'' will continue to work their
magic for the Walt Disney Co. for seven more years.
</P>
<P>
   Harvey and Bob Weinstein will remain co-chairmen of Miramax
Films, which is wholly owned by Disney. The company is one of the
most successful independent film producers, with 148 Academy Award
nominations and 42 Oscars to its credit since the Weinsteins
founded it in 1979.
</P>
<P>
   Disney acquired it in 1993 and agreed to let it operate as an
independently managed production company. Six years ago, Miramax
launched its Dimension Films label, which is responsible for
thriller and action movies such as the ''Scream'' trilogy.
</P>
<P>
   ''Harvey and Bob Weinstein are creative geniuses,'' said Disney
Chairman Michael Eisner.
</P>
<P>
   Along with films, the company in recent years has expanded to
include publishing ''Talk'' magazine, which is edited by former New
Yorker editor Tina Brown. The company also formed a book publishing
business and its own music label.
</P>
<P>
   ''We wouldn't have been able to accomplish this without the
unique combination of autonomy and backing from Disney,'' the
Weinsteins said in a joint statement.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
