<HEADLINE> Devil Rays 8, Rangers 7, 11 Innings  </HEADLINE>
By FRED GOODALL, AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) -- Greg Vaughn homered in the bottom of
the 11th inning to give the Tampa Bay Devil Rays an 8-7 victory
over the Texas Rangers on Thursday night
</P>
<P>
   Vaughn, who homered off Jeff Zimmerman with one out, finished
4-for-6 with three RBIs. He had run-scoring singles in his two
previous at-bats as the Devil Rays ended a four-game losing streak.
</P>
<P>
   Albie Lopez (2-2) pitched three scoreless innings in relief to
get the win after closer Roberto Hernandez couldn't hold a 7-4 lead
in the ninth.
</P>
<P>
   Hernandez, an All-Star last season when he had 43 saves in 47
opportunities, gave up five consecutive singles to allow the
Rangers to wipe out the deficit before Lopez came on to get the
first out of the inning on Chad Curtis' sacrifice bunt.
</P>
<P>
   Rafael Palmeiro, who didn't start because of a slight left
hamstring strain, drove in two of the runs for the Rangers with a
pinch-hit single. Royce Clayton hit a grounder up the middle to
make it 7-7.
</P>
<P>
   It was the fourth time in six tries that Hernandez has not been
able to close out a game this season. Lopez got out of a
base-loaded jam in the ninth by getting David Segui to ground into
a double play.
</P>
<P>
   Zimmerman (0-4), the fifth Texas pitcher, gave up the
game-winning homer on an 0-1 pitch that Vaughn drove into the
left-field stands.
</P>
<P>
   The Devil Rays scored three runs in the seventh on a wild pitch
and RBI singles by Vaughn and John Flaherty to take a 6-4 lead.
Vaughn's RBI single in the eighth gave them the three-run cushion
that Hernandez couldn't protect.
</P>
<P>
   Flaherty snapped an 0-for-16 slump when he homered off Rangers
starter Esteban Loaiza in the second inning. The catcher finished
3-for-5 with two RBIs.
</P>
<P>
   Vinny Castilla hit his fourth homer for the Devil Rays, who are
8-1 when they score seven runs or more and 2-14 when they don't.
</P>
<P>
   Mike Lamb hit his first career homer off Esteban Yan in the
fifth for Texas. Ruben Mateo's three-run shot wiped out a 3-1
deficit in the sixth to extend his career-best hitting streak to
eight games.
</P>
<P>
   Vaughn and Flaherty singled off Crabtree to drive in runs in the
seventh, and the Devil Rays added a third run for a 6-4 lead when
Fred McGriff scored from third base on the reliever's wild pitch.
</P>
<P>
Notes: The matchup between Loaiza and Yan was the first in major
league history between opposing pitchers named Esteban ... Yan
allowed four runs on six hits in 6 2-3 innings. Loaiza gave up four
runs and eight hit in six-plus innings ... Vaughn was the Devil
Rays' designated hitter after starting the team's first 26 games in
left field. ... Segui extended his hitting streak to eight game
with a fourth-inning single ... McGriff has gone 44 at-bats without
a homer since hitting two in Anaheim on April 22.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
