<HEADLINE> Cowboys Release QB Mike Quinn  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS (AP) -- Mike Quinn is out, and Paul Justin is in with the
Dallas Cowboys.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys on Thursday released Quinn after two seasons at
quarterback, giving Justin the No. 2 spot behind Troy Aikman. The
only other quarterback on the roster is Arena and World League
veteran Charles Puleri.
</P>
<P>
   Justin, 31, a five-year veteran, backed up league and Super Bowl
MVP Kurt Warner with the St. Louis Rams last season after starting
quarterback Trent Green tore up his knee in preseason. Justin was
9-of-14 for 91 yards and no touchdowns.
</P>
<P>
   He spent the 1998 season with Cincinnati, playing in five games
with three starts. He completed 34 of 63 passes for 426 yards with
a touchdown and three interceptions.
</P>
<P>
   Justin spent 1995-1997 with the Indianapolis Colts after being
on the Colts' practice squad in 1994. Justin played in 19 games and
started seven, completing 177 of 303 passes for 2,097 yards with
seven touchdowns and seven interceptions.
</P>
<P>
   Quinn, 26, spent one season in Pittsburgh before signing with
Dallas in 1998. That season, he played in three games-- one in the
playoffs -- throwing one pass for a 10-yard gain against the
Philadelphia Eagles.
</P>
<P>
   In another move, the Cowboys waived wide receiver Connie Moore.
</P>
</TEXT>
